34:03.582 --> 34:06.450
Her enemies
<i> are</i> my enemies.

34:06.452 --> 34:08.585
Aw, shit.

34:08.587 --> 34:10.120
God, Donovan.

34:10.122 --> 34:12.522
She loves me, Iris.

34:12.524 --> 34:14.091
And I never stopped
loving her.

34:14.093 --> 34:16.793
Anyone who's against us
is gonna end up in here,

34:16.795 --> 34:18.729
so just keep
that in mind.

34:18.731 --> 34:21.465
There is no us with that bitch.

34:21.467 --> 34:24.868
It's just her and surviving

34:24.870 --> 34:27.371
until she decides it's
time for you to die!

34:27.373 --> 34:29.706
The three of us, together--

34:29.708 --> 34:32.876
it's the only chance
we have to destroy her.

34:32.878 --> 34:36.580
Did you really think the three
of us could ever be partners?

34:36.582 --> 34:38.315
Well, then why did you save me?

34:38.317 --> 34:40.817
I was weak.

34:40.819 --> 34:42.653
I should have
let you die.

34:42.655 --> 34:45.489
(sighs)

34:45.491 --> 34:47.391
No.

34:47.393 --> 34:50.227
You're the one
who's gonna die, son.

34:51.730 --> 34:53.330
You should listen to your mama.

34:53.332 --> 34:55.265
She's right.

34:55.267 --> 34:56.967
Shut up.

34:56.969 --> 34:58.835
Shut up!

34:58.837 --> 35:00.771
Go.

35:00.773 --> 35:03.507
You think
you're her one and only?

35:03.509 --> 35:04.941
That's what you think?

35:04.943 --> 35:07.077
She's already moved on

35:07.079 --> 35:09.446
to the next one;
you can count on it.

35:09.448 --> 35:11.114
You don't know that,

35:11.116 --> 35:12.449
then you're more dumb

35:12.451 --> 35:14.584
than you are pretty.

35:14.586 --> 35:18.989
And you are<i> very</i> pretty.

35:21.493 --> 35:24.361
VALENTINO:<i> It is a world</i>
<i> I no longer recognize</i>

35:24.363 --> 35:28.332
and which no longer
recognizes me.

35:28.334 --> 35:31.168
Anonymity is
your friend.

35:31.170 --> 35:33.270
To survive, we
must be cunning

35:33.272 --> 35:35.272
and stick to
the shadows.

35:35.274 --> 35:38.542
Natacha does not
see it that way.

35:38.544 --> 35:40.444
She has been drawn in
by the future.

35:40.446 --> 35:43.547
This modern world
speaks to her.

35:43.549 --> 35:44.948
I haven't even seen her

35:44.950 --> 35:46.983
since you gave her
that black plastic card.

35:46.985 --> 35:51.121
She speaks of nothing
but shopping and... Uber.

35:51.123 --> 35:54.024
She's costing
me a fortune.

35:54.026 --> 35:56.526
But it's worth
it, I'll admit.

35:56.528 --> 35:59.496
I did it so I could
have you all to myself.

35:59.498 --> 36:01.365
But I thought you loved Natacha.

36:01.367 --> 36:03.200
I loved her
because you did.

36:03.202 --> 36:09.172
And because I was young and
lacking in self-confidence.

36:09.174 --> 36:12.209
I thought I wasn't
woman enough for you.

36:12.211 --> 36:14.478
<i>Bellissima...</i>

36:14.480 --> 36:17.147
you are woman enough
for the both of us.

36:17.149 --> 36:21.518
When I look at you, I see
something of my vanished world.

36:21.520 --> 36:24.221
We can have that world again.

36:24.223 --> 36:25.756
No.

36:27.693 --> 36:29.059
It is lost.

36:29.061 --> 36:30.994
There is no place for
enchantment anymore.

36:30.996 --> 36:32.429
We can make a place.

36:32.431 --> 36:34.598
We can create one.

36:34.600 --> 36:36.400
God knows I've been trying

36:36.402 --> 36:38.702
to recreate you
for the last century.

36:38.704 --> 36:43.006
A series of pale imitations,
gone, or soon to be.

36:43.008 --> 36:45.442
I don't understand.

36:45.444 --> 36:48.178
I've been clearing
the way for us.

36:48.180 --> 36:52.682
We are so close to recapturing
what we once lost.

36:52.684 --> 36:55.018
I'm about to come into
a great deal of money.

36:55.020 --> 36:57.954
We can use it
to turn the Cortez

36:57.956 --> 37:00.924
into a fortress
against the modern world.

37:00.926 --> 37:03.860
A world I hate
even more than you.

37:03.862 --> 37:05.562
And what of Natacha?

37:05.564 --> 37:09.766
If something were
to happen to her...

37:09.768 --> 37:12.135
could you go on?

37:12.137 --> 37:15.372
I would have you
to comfort me.

37:17.810 --> 37:20.143
(door opens)

37:20.145 --> 37:22.245
Little Mouse!

37:22.247 --> 37:24.281
You were so right.

37:24.283 --> 37:27.417
It's astounding what's become
of dusty Beverly Hills.

37:27.419 --> 37:30.220
Shops, shops and more shops.

37:30.222 --> 37:32.322
Rudy, you won't believe
what I found.

37:32.324 --> 37:34.991
A store with your name on it--
"Valentino."

37:34.993 --> 37:36.593
Hmm.

37:36.595 --> 37:38.328
Retail's all well and good,
but for the true couture,

37:38.330 --> 37:39.796
you have to come to my place.

37:39.798 --> 37:41.465
Are you mad?

37:41.467 --> 37:43.233
I'm never stepping foot
in the Cortez again.

37:43.235 --> 37:44.634
James March
is long dead.

37:44.636 --> 37:46.336
You're perfectly safe.

37:46.338 --> 37:49.673
I'll have a car come
pick you up later.

37:52.077 --> 37:54.444
Oh, and, Rudy,
you're not invited.

37:54.446 --> 37:56.613
It's just us
girls tonight.

37:56.615 --> 37:58.081
(chuckles)

38:00.652 --> 38:02.853
(door opens, closes)

38:22.941 --> 38:25.041
If anyone present
knows any reason why

38:25.043 --> 38:27.944
this man and this woman should
not be joined in marriage,

38:27.946 --> 38:30.313
speak now
or forever hold your peace.

38:30.315 --> 38:32.315
Uh... yeah.

38:32.317 --> 38:34.551
Because she's a bitch

38:34.553 --> 38:36.786
with no conscience,
no mercy,

38:36.788 --> 38:38.655
no soul.

38:38.657 --> 38:40.790
(chuckles):
Oh, Liz.

38:40.792 --> 38:42.626
Ignore her. She drinks.

38:42.628 --> 38:44.728
But the law requires a witness.

38:44.730 --> 38:46.029
And I've witnessed plenty.

38:46.031 --> 38:47.397
Please proceed.

38:47.399 --> 38:49.466
I now pronounce you
husband and wife.

38:49.468 --> 38:50.867
You may kiss the bride.

38:50.869 --> 38:52.802
(both laugh)

38:54.506 --> 38:57.507
My men, my family.

38:57.509 --> 39:01.578
I am so happy to finally be
Mrs. Will Drake.

39:01.580 --> 39:03.880
Dad, can I go
upstairs now?

39:03.882 --> 39:05.148
Of course you may.

39:05.150 --> 39:07.250
And I am going to go upstairs

39:07.252 --> 39:09.686
and change out of this
beautiful gown you've made me

39:09.688 --> 39:11.588
and put on
my traveling clothes.

39:11.590 --> 39:14.090
You sure you don't want to have
a drink to celebrate first?

39:14.092 --> 39:16.426
That's what
the honeymoon is for.

39:16.428 --> 39:19.729
I'd like to get that started.
Well, I think I'm going to.

39:19.731 --> 39:22.832
Your wife finds no reason
to object, and you own the bar.

39:22.834 --> 39:24.100
Ah.

39:34.179 --> 39:37.347
My darling Liz.

39:37.349 --> 39:39.449
These are for you,

39:39.451 --> 39:44.187
with my genuine hope that
you someday find true love.

39:44.189 --> 39:46.456
One never knows
when it may appear.

39:51.463 --> 39:54.631
("Fade to Grey" by Visage
playing)

39:54.633 --> 39:58.902
¶ One man on a lonely platform ¶

39:58.904 --> 40:03.106
¶ One case sitting by his side ¶

40:03.108 --> 40:06.977
¶ Two eyes
staring cold and silent ¶

40:06.979 --> 40:09.946
¶ Show fear
as he turns to hide... ¶

40:09.948 --> 40:14.384
Ah, yes! A toast
to the guide of Cortez.

40:14.386 --> 40:17.120
Or as some folks called her,
the bride of Cortez.

40:17.122 --> 40:19.155
March is the name.
Longtime resident.

40:19.157 --> 40:20.657
Call me James.

40:20.659 --> 40:22.325
Mind if I join you?

40:22.327 --> 40:25.228
I understand, uh,
congratulations are in order.

40:25.230 --> 40:26.896
They are indeed, James.

40:26.898 --> 40:28.898
Let's toast
to your good fortune, hmm?

40:28.900 --> 40:31.101
I wouldn't suppose
you have an Armagnac?

40:31.103 --> 40:34.904
I, uh, suspect you do.

40:36.975 --> 40:39.409
Ah.

40:43.148 --> 40:45.148
Here's to new worlds
to conquer.

40:45.150 --> 40:47.717
I will drink to that.

40:49.621 --> 40:51.621
(sighs):
Ah, yes.

40:51.623 --> 40:55.425
We are led by the women
in our lives, are we not?

40:55.427 --> 40:56.626
You know The Countess?

40:56.628 --> 40:58.828
Acquainted, yes.
I never thought

40:58.830 --> 41:00.797
I was the marrying kind,

41:00.799 --> 41:04.434
and now I get to call
that woman my wife.

41:04.436 --> 41:07.303
(laughs)

41:07.305 --> 41:11.675
Felicitations
to the happy couple.

41:11.677 --> 41:13.443
I must commend you.

41:13.445 --> 41:16.346
A blended family
is terribly progressive.

41:16.348 --> 41:17.614
I'm very lucky.

41:17.616 --> 41:19.182
She loves my son
very much.

41:19.184 --> 41:22.318
I, uh...

41:22.320 --> 41:25.221
wasn't referring to your son.

41:25.223 --> 41:27.957
¶ Ah, we fade to grey. ¶

41:29.161 --> 41:31.294
(door creaks)

41:31.296 --> 41:33.163
Initially,
I had my doubts

41:33.165 --> 41:35.699
the child was of my
own flesh and blood.

41:35.701 --> 41:39.235
You see, he doesn't bear any of
the distinctive March features.

41:39.237 --> 41:42.005
Diamond jaw,
strong, piercing eyes.

41:42.007 --> 41:44.674
A flair for
the dramatic.

41:44.676 --> 41:46.242
He has quite a
delicate temperament,

41:46.244 --> 41:47.577
as you'll get to know.

41:47.579 --> 41:49.179
(quiet growling)

41:49.181 --> 41:52.582
Except when
he's feeding.

41:52.584 --> 41:53.983
In that regard,
he most certainly

41:53.985 --> 41:55.351
takes after his mother.

41:55.353 --> 41:57.554
Holy shit!
What the hell is that thing?

41:57.556 --> 41:58.988
COUNTESS:
And to think,

41:58.990 --> 42:01.691
I was prepared
to love and raise<i> your</i> son.

42:01.693 --> 42:03.927
What is going on?

42:03.929 --> 42:06.396
What is this-- some,
some sort of prank?

42:06.398 --> 42:08.598
That thing can't be yours.

42:08.600 --> 42:10.667
It doesn't even look human.

42:10.669 --> 42:12.602
I thought to kill you in Paris,

42:12.604 --> 42:15.071
but I could never stomach
traveling with someone

42:15.073 --> 42:19.576
who said such hateful things
about my child.

42:22.013 --> 42:26.149
I am going to make sure
<i>you</i> suffer, immensely.

42:28.086 --> 42:29.919
(chuckles softly)

42:37.062 --> 42:39.395
RAMONA:
Hey.

42:39.397 --> 42:42.966
Hey.

42:42.968 --> 42:44.467
Are you okay?

42:44.469 --> 42:47.237
Where the hell are we?
Who are you?

42:47.239 --> 42:49.572
One of her victims.

42:49.574 --> 42:50.940
(groans)

42:50.942 --> 42:52.108
Just like you.

42:52.110 --> 42:53.877
(groans)

42:53.879 --> 42:56.379
Uh, this... this is insane.

42:56.381 --> 42:58.281
This can't be real.

42:58.283 --> 43:01.818
You're about to find out
just how real it is,

43:01.820 --> 43:03.453
when they come back down here

43:03.455 --> 43:05.989
and stick you in
that other one.

43:05.991 --> 43:10.326
Please...
get me out of this.

43:10.328 --> 43:12.295
Please!

43:12.297 --> 43:15.064
(panting)

43:15.066 --> 43:17.433
There's a handle
in the back.

43:17.435 --> 43:19.469
Yeah.

43:19.471 --> 43:21.538
(groans):
Oh.

43:24.276 --> 43:26.142
(metallic creaking)
Oh!

43:26.144 --> 43:28.211
(panting)

43:31.750 --> 43:33.516
All right.

43:33.518 --> 43:35.952
All right, it's
gonna be okay.
Oh.

43:35.954 --> 43:38.521
There's got to be
a way out of here.

43:39.624 --> 43:41.090
(sighs)

43:49.467 --> 43:51.467
Hello?!

43:51.469 --> 43:53.536
Is anybody there?!

43:57.475 --> 43:59.475
Help!

43:59.477 --> 44:02.846
Let us out of here!

44:04.983 --> 44:06.716
Help!

44:06.718 --> 44:08.184
Jesus, I think it's soundproof.

44:08.186 --> 44:11.187
No one even knows
we're here.

44:11.189 --> 44:13.022
We'll starve.

44:13.024 --> 44:15.024
I won't.

44:17.495 --> 44:19.996
(gurgling)

44:19.998 --> 44:23.299
(Ramona yelling, Will groaning)

44:32.244 --> 44:34.244
(sobs):
Help me.

44:34.246 --> 44:36.312
Please.

44:36.314 --> 44:38.314
(grunting, gurgling)
